<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<LinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    android:background="#990000"
    android:orientation="vertical"
    tools:context=".introduction">
    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent">

        <LinearLayout
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="match_parent"
            android:layout_marginLeft="10dp"
            android:layout_marginRight="10dp"
            android:background="#ffffff"
            android:orientation="vertical">

            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="15dp"
                android:text="SELF-DEVELOPMENT"
                android:textAlignment="center"
                android:textAllCaps="true"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="30sp"
                android:textStyle="bold" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="15dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Building yourself is very essential, For this chapter i would not be writing much, because psychologically we know what to do to make ourselves better, but i would be give you development tips, that if worked on, can make you edge to success."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="1. Make friends with successful people and occasionally buy them gifts and surprise them with lunch because successful people always give and hardly get, so when you give them, they value the gift a lot."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="2. Get a mentor and follow his instructions and respect the relationship. Never beg your mentor for money or disrespect his or her privacy."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="3. Make new positive friends as often as possible and ensure you keep the communication line open. Create a network of friends and not just connections."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="4.  Show kindness to everyone. Some small boys today will be big boys tomorrow. The biggest dog in the neighbourhood was once a puppy. Keep the information/secret to yourself."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="5. Always plan ahead and be proactive. He that plans the future works less in the future."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:textStyle="italic"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="6. Listen to speeches and messages from great teachers, both religious and educational."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="7. Attend seminars and trainings on any area you need to improve yourself - Train the trainer, personal development, public speaking, sales etc."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="8. Have the habit of keeping a pen and a writing pad handy because ideas come in the form of flashes. The smallest pen is bigger and better than the biggest brain."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="9. Make sure at every point in time you are reading a book. If you spend 20 minutes reading daily, for 52 weeks you would have consumed 1,000,000 words."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="10. Stay away from television as much as possible. You can watch educational channels"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="11. Put control over your mouth; never say evil of any man; what you are not certain of should not be said. Say good of all men."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="12. Always show appreciation for any good deed you received."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="13. Always help someone in need."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="14. Live a debt free life. What you can’t pay cash for is not your size."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="16. Create legitimate multiple sources of income."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp"/>
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="7dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:textStyle="italic"
                android:text="17. Save at least 10 percent of your income."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="18. Invest a portion of your income, and be patient to see it grow. If what you have in your hands is not good to be called a harvest then it’s a seed; sow it."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="19. Keep a good financial record of all income and expenses, so you won’t ask later “where did my money go”"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="20. Be involved in community services, Control traffic, free lesson class for students etc."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="21.  Keep getting better on your daily goals and dream, develop yourself on them and make sure you get to the top 10 % of your industry."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="22. Make sure you engage in physical exercise. It keeps your brain alert and your body fit to enjoy your success."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="23. Pray often, and know that for every success, God made it possible."
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />
            <TextView
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginTop="5dp"
                android:fontFamily="sans-serif"
                android:paddingLeft="8dp"
                android:paddingRight="8dp"
                android:text="Wishing you the very best in life. Practice what you just read, and see the difference your life would record"
                android:textColor="#000000"
                android:textSize="20sp" />

        </LinearLayout>
    </ScrollView>
</LinearLayout>